When tasks are independent, they can be executed concurrently using `Promise.all` in JavaScript to reduce total wait time. For example:
javascript
// Before: Sequential awaits (150ms total if each call takes 50ms)
const user = await getUser(userId);
const settings = await getSettings(userId);
const permissions = await getPermissions(userId);

// After: Concurrent execution (50ms total)
const [user, settings, permissions] = await Promise.all([
  getUser(userId),
  getSettings(userId),
  getPermissions(userId)
]);
